10.40	Sacrifice_in_Maya_culture	Sacrifice in Maya culture	Sacrifice was a religious activity in Maya culture, involving either the killing of animals or the bloodletting by members of the community, in rituals superintended by priests. Sacrifice has been a feature of almost all pre-modern societies at some stage of their development and for broadly the same reason: to propitiate or fulfill a perceived obligation towards the gods.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/Maya-Maske.jpg/200px-Maya-Maske.jpg
